      <h3 class="wow bounceInUp"> WHO ARE WE AND WHAT WE DO</h3>
      <div id="service1" class="d-flex justify-content-sm-start" >
        <div class="w-50 p-3">Flash Pay, a mobile payment service provider that has established a fully licensed back end server platform and system that enables Canadian merchants to accept China RMB payments. Flash Pay facilitates the transfer of payment information between a payment portal (a website - online, or mobile devices - offline) and the Front End Processor or acquiring bank. Flash Pay’s  cashier end total solution gives merchants the capacity and flexibility to accept payment directly from hundreds of thousands Chinese oversea shoppers and travelers.</div>
      </div>


      <div id="service2" class="d-flex justify-content-sm-end">
        <div class="w-50 p-3">Flash Pay offers secure and flexible solutions for online and offline payment processing across a wide variety of markets through retail stores, internet and mobile phone channels. Flash Pay integrates 3rd party payment providers in China that allow Chinese oversea shoppers to pay their purchase offline by being scanned or scanning the QR codes in their mobile devices. Flash Pay then partners with China 3rd party payment providers to automatically convert China RMB into the currencies (Canadian $) that local Canadian stores can accept. </div>
      </div>


      <div id="service3" class="d-flex justify-content-sm-start">
        <div class="w-50 p-3">Flash Pay provides a high security level, handheld smart point-of-sales (POS) terminal to be used in Canadian businesses. It has also partnered with the largest of China’s 3rd party payment providers – Alipay and WeChat Pay - to offer the Chinese traveler to Canada a fully integrated payment solution delivered on their mobile device.</div>
      </div>

